'''圣索菲亚教堂''' ({{lang-el|Ἁγία Σοφία}}；{{lang-tr|Ayasofya}}；Hagia Sophia, Trabzon)，现在是'''圣索菲亚博物馆''',原为[[东正教|东正教]][[教堂|教堂]]，建于1238-1263年<ref>Eastmond, Anthony. "The Byzantine Empires in the Thirteenth Century" in ''Art and Identity in Thirteenth-Century Byzantium: Hagia Sophia and the Empire of Trebizond''. Burlington, VT: Ashgate, 2004, p. 1.</ref>，1584年改为清真寺，位于[[土耳其|土耳其]]东北部[[特拉布宗|特拉布宗]]，中世纪古城以西2英里的[[黑海|黑海]]海岸附近。它是该地区遗留的不多的[[拜占庭帝国|拜占庭帝国]]遗迹之一，被认为是最精美的拜占庭建筑之一<ref>"[http://www.economist.com/news/europe/21582317-fine-byzantine-church-turkey-has-been-converted-mosque-erasing-christian-past Religion in Turkey: Erasing the Christian past] {{Wayback|url=http://www.economist.com/news/europe/21582317-fine-byzantine-church-turkey-has-been-converted-mosque-erasing-christian-past |date=20170315231005 }}." ''[[The_Economist|The Economist]]''. July 25, 2013.</ref>。

